# Meeting Notes

Store written meeting notes and summaries here.

## Purpose

This folder contains:
- Meeting minutes and summaries
- Decision records
- Action item tracking
- Follow-up documentation
- Stakeholder communications

## File Naming Convention

```
YYYY-MM-DD-meeting-type.md

Examples:
2024-08-16-stakeholder-meeting.md
2024-08-20-technical-review.md
2024-08-25-sprint-planning.md
2024-08-30-investor-update.md
```

## Meeting Notes Template

```markdown
# Meeting Notes: [Topic] - [Date]

## Meeting Information
- **Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
- **Time**: HH:MM - HH:MM [Timezone]
- **Type**: Stakeholder/Technical/Planning/Review
- **Location**: In-person/Virtual/Hybrid

## Attendees
- **Present**: 
  - Name 1 (Role)
  - Name 2 (Role)
  - Name 3 (Role)
- **Absent**:
  - Name 4 (Role) - Reason

## Agenda
1. Topic 1
2. Topic 2
3. Topic 3
4. Action Items Review
5. Next Steps

## Discussion Summary

### Topic 1: [Title]
**Presenter**: Name
**Duration**: X minutes

- Key points discussed
- Decisions made
- Questions raised
- Concerns identified

### Topic 2: [Title]
**Presenter**: Name
**Duration**: X minutes

- Key points discussed
- Decisions made
- Questions raised
- Concerns identified

## Decisions Made
1. **Decision**: Description
   - **Rationale**: Why this decision was made
   - **Impact**: Who/what is affected
   - **Timeline**: When to implement

2. **Decision**: Description
   - **Rationale**: Why this decision was made
   - **Impact**: Who/what is affected
   - **Timeline**: When to implement

## Action Items
- [ ] **Action 1** - Assignee: @username - Due: YYYY-MM-DD
- [ ] **Action 2** - Assignee: @username - Due: YYYY-MM-DD
- [ ] **Action 3** - Assignee: @username - Due: YYYY-MM-DD

## Parking Lot
- Issues to be addressed in future meetings
- Questions that need research
- Ideas for future consideration

## Next Meeting
- **Date**: YYYY-MM-DD
- **Agenda Preview**: Main topics for next meeting
- **Preparation Needed**: What attendees should prepare

## Resources and Links
- [Link to presentation slides]
- [Link to shared documents]
- [Link to recording (if available)]
- [Related project issues or tickets]

---

**Meeting Notes prepared by**: [Name]
**Reviewed by**: [Name]
**Distribution**: [List of who should receive these notes]
```

## Meeting Types

### Stakeholder Meetings
- Executive updates
- Investor communications
- Board meetings
- Client/customer meetings

### Technical Meetings
- Architecture reviews
- Code reviews
- Technical planning
- Problem-solving sessions

### Project Management
- Sprint planning
- Sprint reviews
- Retrospectives
- Daily standups (summary notes)

### Strategic Planning
- Product roadmap planning
- Business strategy sessions
- Market analysis discussions
- Competitive analysis

## Best Practices

### During the Meeting
- Take notes in real-time
- Capture decisions and rationale
- Record action items with assignees
- Note parking lot items
- Ask for clarification when needed

### After the Meeting
- Review and clean up notes within 24 hours
- Send to all attendees for review
- Update project tracking systems
- Schedule follow-up meetings if needed

### Follow-up
- Track action item completion
- Send reminders for upcoming deadlines
- Archive completed action items
- Prepare agenda for next meeting

---

**Effective meeting notes ensure decisions are documented, action items are tracked, and everyone stays aligned on project progress.**